<TEXT>
three robbers burst into a fastfood 
restaurant tied up the manager and attempted to flee with 
thousands of dollars but were cut down and killed in a fusillade 
of police gunfire monday authorities said 
a fourth person involved in the robbery at a mcdonalds 
restaurant was wounded said police lt fred nixon none of the 
victims was immediately identified but nixon said the survivor was 
in serious condition at a los angeles hospital 
nine officers from the police departments special 
investigations section watched the robbery taking place around 2 
am and approached the men after they got into a getaway car 
authorities said 
the officers opened fire when one of the four raised what looked 
like a handgun and pointed it at them said police lt bill hall 
who heads the team that investigates shootings involving police 
all officers fired almost simultaneously said hall 
the gun turned out to be a pellet gun but to police it looked 
real he said i dont think youd be likely to know the 
difference if you were looking down the barrel of one hall said 
officers recovered masks and several thousand dollars in cash 
from the car hall said 
police had been following the four some of whom were believed 
involved in earlier restaurant robberies said officer bill frio 
we had a couple of possible suspects identified but not 
enough evidence to arrest and book them so we were tailing them 
he said 
the four were followed from the beachfront community of venice 
to sun valley about 15 miles north of downtown where hall said 
officers watched them enter the closed restaurant 
there was a female manager inside alone and the doors were 
all locked said hall the suspects forced open a side door 
tied her up and forced her to provide the combination of the safe 
hall said the manager called police when she saw the men 
approaching her restaurant but it was decided to make the arrest 
afterward rather than interrupt the robbery because there had been 
no injuries in previous restaurant holdups 
</TEXT>
