<TEXT>
the associated press has named a new executive 
photo editor and a presidential assistant to coordinate its 
recently announced electronic darkroomphotostream project 
president louis d boccardi said vincent j alabiso will become 
executive photo editor of the news cooperative and harold g buell 
will be assistant to the president for electronic darkrooms and 
photostream 
alabiso director of photography for the boston globe and a 
former new england photo editor in the aps boston bureau succeeds 
buell who has directed ap photo operations since 1968 
the appointments announced monday are effective march 19 
the ap announced last month that it will be installing 
electronic darkrooms at its 950 laserphoto members these darkrooms 
will provide newspapers with aps highspeed digital photostream 
system that will enable them to receive an ap black and white photo 
in less than a minute and a color photo in three minutes 
hal buell has contributed enormously to the growth of our 
photo service which now reaches 950 newspapers in the united 
states alone i have asked him to bring that experience to the 
implementation of our photostream and darkroom projects which are 
the most exciting steps we have taken in photos in recent 
history boccardi said 
and in vin alabiso we bring back to the ap an outstanding 
photo editor who has now seen what we do from the newspapers 
perspective 
these moves supported by the outstanding photo team we have 
in place position us for the exciting years that lie ahead in the 
world of highspeed highquality news photography 
buell 58 who has a masters degree from the medill school of 
journalism at northwestern university which he also attended as an 
undergraduate has been in the photo department since 1957 he was 
named executive photo editor in 1968 and the title of assistant 
general manager was added in 1977 
he has been instrumental in the concept and development of the 
photostream system 
alabiso 43 has been director of photography at the globe since 
january 1987 a 1969 graduate from northeastern university in 
boston alabiso joined the ap in new york in 1975 and left the 
following year 
he rejoined the ap in boston in 1981 as photo editor and was 
named new england newsphoto editor in 1983 before leaving in 1986 
to join the globe 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

