us honey production dropped 21 percent last 
year to 169 million pounds according to a report by the 
agriculture department 
about 33 million colonies produced honey in 1989 a 3 percent 
increase from 1988 the report said but the average yield per 
colony was only 511 pounds down from 663 pounds in 1988 
adverse conditions were encountered in most states and 
included wet weather restrictions on movement early in the year 
dry weather disease and mite infestations throughout the year 
