of arizona said monday 
the fda last month withdrew its approval of the device both as a 
permanent implant and as a temporary bridge to transplantation 
saying there were serious deficiencies with its manufacture 
the agency also withdrew its approval of the acute ventricular 
assist device which helps the natural heart pump 
the artificial heart was initially called the jarvik7 but 
jarvik no longer is associated with symbion inc of tempe ariz 
which markets the product as the symbion7 symbion also markets 
the second device 
university medical center said in a statement monday that the 
fda now would not object to the devices being used as a last resort 
if all other approved alterntative treatments have failed or were 
deemed inappropriate and when no other lifesaving device is 
available to save a patients life 
in response to last months decision dr jack g copeland 
director of the medical centers artificial heart and transplant 
