national park said monday after a day of ground and aerial 
surveillance led rescuers to areas deemed remotely possible where 
they could have been 
they indicated quite a number of places haney said we 
dug down with no positive results it all brings us back to this 
one massive slide path 
officials called sundays avalanche one of the largest in recent 
history 
mondays search was hampered by snow driven by a biting wind 
that sent temperatures plunging four tracking dogs searched a 
6milelong trail for any scent of the four along the slopes about 
50 miles west of calgary 
the avalanche path itself looked like a lunar landscape with 
some snow slabs the size of my truck said reporter chris dawson 
of the calgary herald it was an absolutely sobering experience 
i can tell you my heart was in my throat 
the searchers expected to advance short distances today and 
shove long thin hightension rods into the snow until they reach 
