<TEXT>
gen michel aoun called up reserve forces 
today in apparent preparation for an assault to overrun part of the 
christian enclave north of beirut and cripple a rival christian 
militia 
aouns gunners and militiamen of samir geageas lebanese forces 
dueled with howitzers and mortars in east beirut and the 
snowblanketed mountains northeast of the capital in the 15th day 
of the intrachristian showdown 
the lebanese red cross committee issued radio appeals for urgent 
blood donations and police reported early in the day that rescuers 
removed 18 rotting corpses from east beirut streets 
a police spokesman who cannot be named in line with 
regulations said nine people were killed and 22 wounded in the 
fighting today between aouns fighters and geageas militiamen in 
east beirut and kesrouan province 
by police count the overall toll stood at 498 killed and 1724 
wounded since the struggle began jan 30 for domination of the 
310squaremile christian enclave 
geagea in an interview with the arabic service of radio monte 
carlo said monday he had talked to aoun by telephone and asked for 
peace negotiaions 
i told the general that we should negotiate to put an end to 
this useless war but i cannot accept to be annihilated geagea 
said he did not say when the conversation took place 
the command of aouns estimated 19000strong army in a 
communique called up reservists and volunteers who received 
training in the use of weapons during a sixmonth confrontation 
with the syrians last summer 
the additional fighters the communique said will be 
immediately armed to join their units it did not give further 
details 
aoun is believed to have a reserve force of about 2000 retired 
military personnel in addition to a 4000 volunteerreserve 
fighters 
beiruts prestigious annahar newspaper said the intrachristian 
confrontation was heading for a swift conclusive battle 
it said aoun wanted to overrun the kesrouan province a 
traditional stronghold for geageas 6000strong militia to seize 
the harbor facilities and central bank offices in jounieh 12 
miles from beirut 
military sources speaking on condition of anonymity also said 
aoun appeared determined to dislodge geageas militia from its main 
power base in kesrouan 
one source said aouns gunners were maintaining artillery 
barrages and a series of hitandrun attacks against the militia in 
kesrouan to run down their enemys ammunition and effort before 
the major battle 
there have been no significant gains in territory since the 
confrontation shifted to the kesrouan province on saturday the 
source noted 
police reported civilians were fleeing the mountain resorts of 
ajaltoun bekfaya and daraya despite heavy snows to escape the 
battle everybody seems to expect 
president elias hrawi appealed monday to the superpowers france 
and the vatican to support possible intervention by his 
syrianbacked troops to halt the fighting 
hrawi made a similar appeal last week beirut newspapers said 
pope john paul ii and france traditional protector of lebanons 
christians warned against syrian military intervention 
aoun does not recognize hrawis christianmoslem government 
which is backed by syria he also has vowed to drive the syrians 
who support the moslem militias of west beirut from lebanon 
</TEXT>
