<TEXT>
here are some facts and figures about tadzhikistan 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the land tadzhikistan covers 55240 square miles bordered on 
the north by uzbekistan and the kirghiz republic the east by 
chinese turkestan and the south by afghanistan its huge mountain 
glaciers are the source of many rapid rivers and the republic 
contains rich pasture lands 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the people nearly 60 percent of the republics 48 million 
residents are tadzhiks who speak an iranian dialect little 
different from persian but most tadzhiks are sunni moslems not 
shiites like the iranians about 23 percent of the people are 
uzbeks who live in the northwest and 105 percent are russian or 
ukrainian 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the economy the major occupations are farming horticulture 
and cattle breeding but large industrial enterprises have been 
established that include mining and textile factories tadzhikistan 
produces apricots olives figs olives pomegranates and many 
other kinds of fruit the gissar sheep is famous for its meat and 
fat and the karakul for its wool 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
history tadzhiks are considered the descendants of the 
original aryan population of turkestan the tadzhik soviet 
socialist republic was formed from those regions of bokhara and 
turkestan where most of the population was tadzhik and became part 
of the soviet union on dec 5 1929 
</TEXT>
