<TEXT>
the fourmasted squarerigger moshulu the 
last winner of the great grain race around cape horn and a fixture 
on the waterfront for years is expected to be returned to sailing 
condition and leave the city 
one possible new berth for the 394foot barkentine the largest 
of its kind still afloat is san francisco its home port when it 
sailed under a us flag according to a spokesman for the owner 
the 86yearold tall ship has been a restaurant at penns 
landing since 1976 last july its plush interior was heavily 
damaged by a fire and the black ironhulled ship has been boarded 
up for months 
a spokesman for the owner specialty restaurants inc of 
