below zero in the afternoon and duluth minn had a wind chill 
reading of 43 below zero 
temperatures were below freezing at midday from the northern and 
central high plains to upper michigan and northern lower michigan 
and below zero across parts of montana north dakota and minnesota 
but temperatures remained mild east of the cold air mass and 
mansfield ohio had a record 56 degrees while green bay wis 
tied its record of 43 
strong gusty wind also ushered cold air into the southwest 
heavy snow fell across wyoming late monday and early tuesday 
including 15 inches at big horn 11 inches at rawlins and 10 
inches at casper and dayton 
heavy snow also fell across parts of western south dakota with 
up to 9 inches reported in the black hills area 
snow advisories were posted for parts of utah and colorado 
snow also fell across parts of the northwest with snow reported 
at elevations near sea level as far south as northern california 
where snow was reported at arcata and redding during the morning 
newport on the central coast of oregon got 2 inches of snow 
overnight 
redding tied its record low for the date of 26 degrees 
snow was expected in northern arizona by wednesday and a winter 
storm watch was issued for wednesday at higher elevations 
strong southerly winds prevailed ahead of the arctic cold front 
from the southern plains and the lower mississippi valley to the 
northeast 
winds gusted to 54 mph during the morning at burlington vt 
and to 52 mph at erie pa 
strong westerly winds blew through the high mountain passes of 
extreme southwestern texas guadalupe pass reported winds at 56 mph 
during the afternoon with gusts to 69 mph 
