a police patrol near san martin de pangoa 175 miles east of lima 
in the jungle left five guerrillas dead and one policeman wounded 
also monday police said guerrillas fatally shot two policemen 
in piura two others in huacho and one in chiclayo 
huacho and chiclayo are on the pacific coast northwest of lima 
and piura is in the northern coastal desert 
the interior ministry said police tuesday captured four men with 
printing equipment and thousands of counterfeit tickets to soccer 
games at the national stadium and bullfights at limas historic 
acho bull ring 
they identified the four as working for the shining path and 
said the tickets were sold to raise money for guerrilla operations 
police said the four also produced thousands of falsified 
identification cards for providing aliases to shining path members 
to escape police detection 
the maoinspired shining path launched its armed insurgency in 
1980 near ayacucho 235 miles southeast of lima in the andean 
highlands the group now operates through much of the highlands and 
the cocaproducing jungles of the northeast where drug traffickers 
pay them to provide protection from police authorities say 
the government says more than 17500 people have died in the 
decade of violence including police soldiers rebels government 
officials and civilians 
