<TEXT>
the four allied powers that defeated nazi 
germany in world war ii have maintained their rights as victors 
and 45 years later still have the final say on the reunification of 
the divided nation 
the disclosure in ottawa that the united states soviet union 
britain and france had agreed to a twostage plan for reunification 
provides the international framework to close the long final 
chapter of the war 
a peace treaty has never been signed between the four powers and 
germany even though all four ended their state of war with the 
country during the 1950s 
differences between the western powers and the soviet union over 
germany led to some of the tensest episodes of the postwar era 
such as the western airlift in 194849 that broke the soviet 
attempt to isolate west berlin 
in 1961 east germany built the berlin wall which only began to 
be dismantled last year around west berlin to stop the flow of 
east germans to the west that exodus was threatening to deprive 
the communist state of some of its most skilled workers 
at the end of world war ii britain the soviet union and the 
united states agreed pending a peace settlement that some former 
german territories in the east would be taken over by poland and 
the soviet union many germans living there fled to the west 
east and west germany joined in the 35nation helsinki accords 
of 1975 that specified european borders could be changed only 
peacefully and west germany has signed separate treaties with the 
soviet union and poland that addressed the border issues 
but not all german political parties have renounced claims to 
the eastern territories and any peace agreement would be expected 
to put the issue to rest 
the zones occupied by the victors after the war became the 
modern states of east and west germany the germany democratic 
republic in the eastern soviet zone and the federal republic of 
germany in the western zones 
over the years the four powers have forsaken most of their 
occupying rights in east and west germany but a number of 
anomalies remain and the victors continue to oversee berlin 
berlin deep inside east germany is divided into four sectors 
each controlled by one of the powers the british french and us 
sectors make up west berlin and the soviet sector is east berlin 
which east germany claims as its capital 
armed forces of the four powers retain and exercise their rights 
to patrol in the other sectors the western powers refuse to 
recognize east german authority in east berlin and officially 
insist on resolving any disputes with soviet officers 
the four powers military units also have rights to patrol in 
east and west germany 
the western powers require east and west germany to run troop 
trains to ferry any of their military between west germany and 
berlin east germany must allow access through three corridors 
across its territory to berlin 
the military forces of britain france and the united states 
remain concentrated in the zones once occupied by the victors now 
allied with west germany through the north atlantic treaty 
organization 
the western powers also have maintained exclusive rights to fly 
commercial planes into berlin from the west although west germany 
has recently obtained some rights for joint flights 
reluctance of the western powers to recognize the east german 
state created under the auspices of the soviets was one of the 
obstacles to german membership in the united nations east and west 
germany didnt join the united nations until 1973 
one of the last joint enterprises of the four powers was 
imprisoning rudolf hess a deputy to hitler whom they took turns 
guarding in spandau prison in berlin until he died in 1987 at age 
93 
