<TEXT>
more young americans today love 
humor if it is gruesome targets women or is lowkey according to 
a psychologist who studied what made college students laugh 
james carroll a psychology professor at central michigan 
university said tuesday that students 25 years ago disapproved of 
the gruesome humor that is now widely accepted 
gary larsons cartoon the far side which occasionally 
portrays animals eating humans is an example of gruesome humor so 
are helen keller jokes and dead baby jokes carroll said 
college students 25 years ago did not endorse that kind of humor 
but it seems more acceptable today 
mel helitzer a journalism professor who teaches a course in 
humor at ohio university in athens ohio said societal attitudes 
have changed more than have individual tastes 
its more of a public acceptance helitzer said humor is 
criticism and we tend to make jokes about things that bother us 
like dan quayle 
carroll administered the institute for personality and ability 
testing humor test of personality to 79 college students in fall 
1988 the original test was administered in 1963 to 200 students by 
raymond cattell at the university of illinois results of carrolls 
study were published in the december 1989 issue of psychological 
reports 
the test asks subjects to respond to 150 jokes and cartoons as 
either funny or dull he correlated the results with 12 dimensions 
of humor and compared the findings to the 1963 results of the same 
test 
what we once called blue humor or hard core is being accepted 
today said helitzer who had not reviewed the study 
carroll said his study found college students of both sexes have 
changed in their appreciation of humor for instance the 1963 
study indicated that 40 percent to 45 percent of all students 
appreciated humor directed at women that figure rose to about 70 
percent of all students in the 1988 study 
it may be that the society is more open carroll said 
his study also found that women are finding jokes about 
themselves funny and people like lowkey controlled humor like 
that of comedians david letterman and arsenio hall 
