modernizing its nuclear missiles capable of reaching us soil 
in his proposed 1991 budget presented to congress jan 29 bush 
set pentagon spending at 292 billion for the fiscal year that 
starts oct 1 thats a nominal increase from the 287 billion to 
be spent in the current budget year but is a 2 percent decline 
after the effect of inflation 
bush foresees similar cuts in each of the next several years 
but critics say the pace is far too slow in light of the 
