<TEXT>
wellsgardner electronics corp manufactured 
televisions before the japanese were even a blip on the industry 
screen now theyre hoping to stage a comeback with a new line of 
usmade sets 
the accent is decidedly american in the companys deal with 
majestic industries inc a yearold marylandbased independent 
distributor managed by a team of former rca executives 
stamped made in america the new televisions will be built 
at wellsgardners plant on chicagos northwest side and marketed 
to middle america rural residents and suburbanites who prefer 
oldfashioned consolemodel tv sets 
some parts will be made in places like taiwan mexico and 
malaysia but the full assembly process will take place at the 
275000 squarefoot plant richard conquest the companys chief 
financial officer said in a telephone interview monday 
the company doesnt have any intention of trying to compete 
headon against japanese giants like sony and mitsubishi conquest 
said instead he said wellsgardner simply wants to get back into 
a business where it once played a leading role supplying 
privatelabel televisions 
thats our cup of tea conquest said were really excited 
about it 
the threeyear wellsgardner contract is designed to fill an 
industry void said james schwab president of majestic 
what we saw was that with the basic marketing most television 
manufacturing was aimed at the top 200300 retailers so their 
sales planning and product offerings were aimed at the top 
retailers he said 
this left a void with the independent retailer who needs 
local support from an independent distributor schwab said 
seventy percent of the sets wellsgardner plans to make will be 
traditional console models they will be sold under the majestic 
name through independent dealers rather than mass retailers like 
sears roebuck and co and jc penney co 
production starts this week with 24000 to 30000 sets 
scheduled to be built in the first year conquest said the sets 
should become available to consumers within a month 
it will add approximately 10 million to our 1990 sales 
conquest said that would represent about 30 percent of 1989s 
estimated sales of 35 million for now wellsgardner doesnt have 
any plans to build tvs for other distributors officials said but 
the company might consider similar deals in the future with 
retailers like highland silo and fretters 
wellsgardner was founded in 1924 as a radio manufacturer 
the company diversified in the television age and was one of the 
first makers of blackandwhite sets it was a major manufacturer 
of sets sold in stores like sears and penneys conquest said 
then in the 1970s the japanese came in and we got out of the 
tv business he said explaining that the company couldnt 
compete with cheaper overseas labor costs 
at the end of the 1970s the company decided to try again and 
began assembling sets for fujitsus teknika division 
but the japanese company deterred by high import duties and 
us labor costs decided not to renew the contract in 1988 
conquest said 
in the meantime wellsgardner has focused its energies on 
making monitors for coinoperated video games which account for 
about 60 percent of its sales 
it hopes the new deal will bring stability and help reduce its 
dependence on the cyclical video game industry said president 
frank j myers 
the company rejoins an industry now dominated by foreignowned 
firms like rca and sony and glenview illbased zenith 
electronics corp 
zenith is the only remaining americanowned manufacturer of 
color tvs that also makes most of its parts said bob violino 
associate editor at television digest a weekly newsletter that 
tracks the consumer electronics industry 
only a handful of smaller firms like wellsgardner also 
assemble their own sets in this country he said 
wellsgardners reentry wont cut into any of these other 
companies shares violino said 
zenith does not expect the move to affect its business company 
spokesman john taylor said 
</TEXT>
