<TEXT>
source perrier sas lions share of the us bottled water 
market could begin to evaporate if its recall of the popular 
perrier brand because of benzene contamination lasts for two 
months marketing experts say 
the bubbly water is being kept out of stores restaurants and 
bars in the united states and canada after north carolina officials 
found some bottles tainted with small amounts of benzene 
perrier said it believes an employee mistakenly used a product 
containing the cancercausing chemical to clean grease from one 
bottling line whose production was destined only for north 
america a spokesman for the french health ministry said there was 
no contamination at the spring from which the sparkling water flows 
although the benzene levels were relatively low about two to 
four times the five parts per billion level allowable under food 
and drug administration standards perrier said it requested the 
recall late friday to restore consumer confidence 
the companys us subsidiary perrier group of america inc 
said monday it expects to keep the product out of us and canadian 
markets for up to two or three months however a spokesman for the 
parent company in paris said the green bottles could be back on 
north american store shelves in a week or two 
the timing is more of a problem than the benzene said al 
ries chairman of trout amp ries inc a greenwich conn marketing 
strategy firm 
he said the absence of perrier for any extended time will 
severely test the loyalty of many consumers who may be used to 
drinking the sparking water several times a week 
perrier which turned bottled water into a status symbol several 
years ago accounts for nearly a quarter of the estimated 22 
billion in annual bottled water sales in the united states 
according to the new yorkbased beverage marketing corp 
brands are badges said ries by that i mean when you sit 
at a restaurant table and order a brand by name it says something 
about you personally not being available will force the consumer 
to ask for another brand name and the smart competitior is going 
to move in 
gary m stibel principal of new england consulting group of 
westport conn agreed its a godsend trial opportunity for its 
competitors if theyre smart enough to take advantage of it 
but experts questioned whether the numerous other smaller 
bottled water companies were strong enough to fill the temporary 
void left by perrier 
no one in the marketplace has seen fit to build a strong no 2 
brand in america if perrier goes flat said riesdistribution 
is the key the product has to be out there and the product has to 
be widely available 
there are about 450 water bottling plants in the united states 
producing more than 600 different brand labels of drinking water 
natural water and spring water according to bevmark inc a los 
angelesbased consulting firm in addition there are more than 50 
brands of imported waters bevmark said 
perrier also markets poland spring calistoga and arrowhead 
bottled waters 
key brand competitors include evian and saratoga both owned by 
bsn of france and san pellegrino of italy 
david s daniel chief executive officer of evian waters of 
france inc said his company had no intention of capitalizing on 
perriers problems although it plans to launch a major new 
advertising campaign in the next two weeks he said it was 
coincidence the campaign was starting right after the perrier 
recall 
right now we dont see any real need to change our strategy or 
adjust our spending daniel said its pretty much business as 
usual 
many marketing experts likened perriers problem to that of 
johnson amp johnson which recalled its tylenol pain killer in 1982 
after some capsules were tainted with cyanide resulting in several 
deaths 
some of the marketers criticized perriers relatively lowkey 
public relations approach to the problem which seemed to contrast 
with johnson amp johnsons fullscale public information campaign 
that campaign was credited with helping the company regain market 
share following the tylenol scare 
but others said perriers total recall even though only a 
dozen bottles were believed to be contaminated was more than 
enough to reassure consumers 
