<DOCNO> AP900213-0205 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
safeway stores plans to issue a modest 
amount of stock to the public marks the beginning of the final 
chapter in one of the nations most successful leveraged buyouts 
i dont know of any leveraged buyouts that have numbers like 
they have said brian suher an analyst with the brokerage black 
amp co in portland ore 
suher was referring to safeways reduction of a staggering 57 
billion buyout debt to 31 billion and its surging operating 
profits in the past year the oaklandbased chain achieved the 
turnaround largely by eliminating its least profitable stores in 
reducing the size of the chain from 2326 stores to 1117 
analysts for the past year have praised the buyout for forcing 
safeway to accelerate a restructuring and trim itself quickly to 
its most profitable core 
chairman and chief executive peter magowan recently boasted that 
although sales last year were 143 billion safeways operating 
income was greater than when it posted annual sales of 20 billion 
those numbers are the stuff of dreams that fueled the buyout 
craze of the 1980s 
in a leveraged buyout a small group of investors acquires a 
company in a transaction financed largely by borrowing the debt 
often nearly crippling is repaid with money generated by the 
acquired companys operations or the sale of its assets 
the lbo as its commonly known is often used by management to 
retain control of a company threatened by a hostile suitor the 
idea is for the company to reemerge later as a public one 
stronger and more profitable and thereby less subject to takeovers 
the ability of a company to reenter the public market also is 
crucial to managers hopes of eventually cashing in their stakes 
and reaping big profits from the turnaround 
the stock sale announced monday and the first since the nov 
30 1986 buyout was a show of confidence by the nations 
thirdlargest supermarket chain 
the offering of 10 million shares of new common stock will sell 
for between 13 and 16 a share after the offering the company 
will have 100 million shares outstanding 
company officials and those at kohlberg kravis roberts amp co 
the new york investment firm that managed the buyout said monday 
they could not comment publicly on the offering because of 
restraints by the securities and exchange commission 
the remaking of safeway began in july 1986 with a hostile tender 
offer from the dart group corp led by herbert and robert haft 
that attempt forced safeway to agree to be acquired by kohlberg 
kravis that fall for 69 a share the deal left safeway management 
in command and offered certain officers the right to buy 10 percent 
of the now closely held concern 
the deal also left safeway burdened with debt a staggering 45 
in debt for each dollar in equity one of the highest such ratios 
ever in a large deal 
to restore profitability safeway has been building larger 
stores called super stores that offer specialty departments 
such as bakeries delicatessens pharmacies seafood counters and 
floral and wine shops 
to offer more services and longer hours safeway employees 
hours have gone up 23 percent per store in the past two years 
safeway was able to win significant contract concessions from its 
unions and wages are now only slightly higher than in 1986 
the buyout has been lauded as mutually beneficial by both 
safeway and kohlberg krravis which also acquired rjr nabisco in 
the nations biggest leveraged buyout after a fierce bidding 
contest 
in most cases safeway sold operations that were 
underperforming exceptions were safeway stores in britain which 
garnered a strong price and 172 southern california stores sold to 
the von cos in a 408 million deal that transaction also made 
safeway the largest shareholder in vons the biggest supermarket 
chain in the los angeles area 
the performance improvement is nothing short of sensational 
but more importantly the public has endorsed their operating 
formats suher said 
theyre having marvelous increases because they have changed 
from a behemoth that was insensitive to a corporation very very 
sensitive to consumers and communities 
safeway finished the year with a 3 million profit on 143 
billion in sales its first profitable year since the buyout 
operating profits jumped 42 percent for the year to 463 
million and 805 percent in the fourth quarter to 139 million 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

